    ImageSize->{22.109375, 21.}], "InlineCode"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a528c13e-0657-4f4a-8e89-f93f4141fd7e"],
 "\[VeryThinSpace] icon. On the desktop, go to the Help menu."
}], "Answer",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"a60dcaf5-6918-4486-a4fc-fbf4ed48ca70"],

Cell["How do I try examples in the documentation?", "Question",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"90bd6888-627a-4705-91c2-92660d1a31a8"],

Cell["\<\
Often you can just run them right inside the documentation. Alternatively, \
copy them to your working notebook and run them there.\
\>", "Answer",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"e5a86478-ac40-4020-97a4-1d0f65952cd4"],

Cell["How long does it take to learn the whole Wolfram Language?", "Question",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"1c0b1a55-2bc9-4bec-927d-f3f605e51f74"],

Cell["\<\
As in learning a human language, it takes some time to become fluent, and to \
know the principles of the language. One can go on learning specific \
vocabulary almost indefinitely.\
\>", "Answer",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"743610ab-cc07-4997-8fd8-548bd65f07ca"],

Cell["\<\
How much of the Wolfram Language does one need to know to use it in practice?\
\
\>", "Question",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"2f03ba10-783e-4344-a2d5-990016fdb5bf"],

Cell["\<\
One needs to know its principles, as they are covered, for example, in this \
book. As with a human language, one can have a comparatively small working \
vocabulary, not least because there are usually many ways to express a given \
thing. It\[CloseCurlyQuote]s easy to expand vocabulary in any particular case \
just by looking at documentation.\
\>", "Answer",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"17f2e851-8832-4b21-9af8-8a2dd8567c32"],

Cell["\<\
How can I read Wolfram Language code if I\[CloseCurlyQuote]m not fluent in \
English?\
\>", "Question",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"81523a07-f80d-4680-bee9-7ce70bd28f84"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "It\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll help if you switch on ",
 StyleBox["code captions",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[LongDash]which give short descriptions for every function name that \
appears, and are available for many languages. "
}], "Answer",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"03a46535-d009-4050-ac7d-d6b4cbcc1a8d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Tech Note", "TechNoteSection",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"ad788197-42b3-49b5-9200-c394a3495910"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There\[CloseCurlyQuote]s computable data about the structure of the Wolfram \
Language right in the Wolfram Language, accessible from ",
 ButtonBox["WolframLanguageData",
  BaseStyle->"Link"],
 "."
}], "TechNote",
 Editable->False,
 Deletable->False,
 ShowCellBracket->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"a6341bce-fea3-4e99-b9c2-78509ccb6769"]
}, Open  ]],

